{"lemma": "وَيْحَ", "slug": "وَيْحَ", "root": "#.#.ح", "root_slug": "_-_-ح", "root_link": "/words/roots/_-_-ح", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": false}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n42417"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%88%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92%D8%AD%D9%8E"}}, "translations": {"en": "woe to", "fa": "وای بر", "ur": "افسوس", "tr": "vah", "id": "celaka", "bn": "হায়", "es": "ay de", "fr": "malheur à", "de": "Wehe", "ru": "горе", "zh": "祸哉"}, "definition": null, "etymology": null, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n42417", "headword_ar": "وَيْحٌ", "root": "wyH", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "a word denoting compassion, or pity: (AZ, As, S, K:)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wayolN", "text_ar": "وَيْلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "denotes [an imprecation of] punishment; (S;) or [of] removal from good, or from prosperity: (AZ, As:) or [of] destruction: (AZ:) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wayosN", "text_ar": "وَيْسٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "denotes the same as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wyH", "text_ar": "ويح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (AZ;) or less than"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wyH", "text_ar": "ويح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (As:) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wyH", "text_ar": "ويح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wys", "text_ar": "ويس"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "denote compassion, or pity, and admiration of one's beauty; as when you say of a child,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wayoHahu maA A^amolaHahu", "text_ar": "وَيْحَهُ مَا اَمْلَحَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wayosahu mA AmlHh", "text_ar": "وَيْسَهُ ما املحه"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Mercy on him!"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or the like:"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "how beautiful is he!"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] (Kh) or, accord. to most of the lexicologists,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wyl", "text_ar": "ويل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is a word said to, or of, any one who falls into destruction or trial, or misfortune, and on whom one does not wish God's mercy: and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wyH", "text_ar": "ويح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is said to, or of, any one who falls into trial or misfortune, and for whom one wishes God's mercy, and his escape therefrom: the former word being so used in the Kur-án, and the latter by the Prophet: (T:) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wyl", "text_ar": "ويل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is said to, or of, him who falls into destruction: and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wyH", "text_ar": "ويح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is a word by which one chides him who is at the point of falling into destruction: (Sb:) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wyH", "text_ar": "ويح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wyl", "text_ar": "ويل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "are syn., (Yz, En-Nadr, S, Ibn-Et-Faraj,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wys", "text_ar": "ويس"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies the same: (Ibn-El-Faraj:) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wyH", "text_ar": "ويح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is a little softer, or more gentle, than"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wyl", "text_ar": "ويل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (En-Nadr:) [if so,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wayoHahu", "text_ar": "وَيْحَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "woe to him:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in the same, or in a milder, manner than"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wayolahu", "text_ar": "وَيْلَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":] or the original of"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 2971}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wyH", "text_ar": "ويح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wayo", "text_ar": "وَيْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; sometimes"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "H", "text_ar": "ح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "being added to this latter word, and sometimes"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "l", "text_ar": "ل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and sometimes"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "b", "text_ar": "ب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and sometimes"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "s", "text_ar": "س"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (K;) so that it becomes"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wyH", "text_ar": "ويح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wyl", "text_ar": "ويل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wyb", "text_ar": "ويب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wys", "text_ar": "ويس"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) [See"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wyl", "text_ar": "ويل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wyb", "text_ar": "ويب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wys", "text_ar": "ويس"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wy", "text_ar": "وي"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] You say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wayoHN", "text_ar": "وَيْحٌ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lizayodK", "text_ar": "لِزَيْدٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Mercy on Zeyd!"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "woe to Zeyd!"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; putting"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wyH", "text_ar": "ويح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in the nom. case as an inchoative; (S, K;) and in like manner,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wayolN lizayodK", "text_ar": "وَيْلٌ لِزَيْدٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S:) and also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wayoHFA lizayodK", "text_ar": "وَيْحًا لِزَيْدٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; putting"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wyH", "text_ar": "ويح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in the acc. case because of a verb understood; (S, K;) as though you said"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^alozamahu A@ll~`hu wayoHFA", "text_ar": "اَلْزَمَهُ ا@للّٰهُ وَيْحًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "May God make mercy,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "woe, to attend him constantly!"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; and in like manner,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wayolFA lizayodK", "text_ar": "وَيْلًا لِزَيْدٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S:) or [it is put in the acc. case as an absolute complement of a verb understood, i. e., as an inf. n., and] the meaning is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^ataraH~amuhu taraH~umFA", "text_ar": "اَتَرَحَّمُهُ تَرَحُّمًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I say, May God have mercy on him! emphatically"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (Z, in the Fáïk:) you also say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wayoHaka", "text_ar": "وَيْحَكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wayoHa zayodK", "text_ar": "وَيْحَ زَيْدٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (S, K;) making"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wyH", "text_ar": "ويح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "a prefixed n.; (S;) and putting it in the acc. case again because of a verb understood; (S, K;) and in like manner,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wayolaka", "text_ar": "وَيْلَكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wayola zayodK", "text_ar": "وَيْلَ زَيْدٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S:) and also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wayoHamaA zayodK", "text_ar": "وَيْحَمَا زَيْدٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in the same sense. (K.)"}], "source_refs": ["AZ", "As", "S", "K", "Kh", "T", "Sb"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}